OL,7,FJudge Potter told Harper: "I am sure
OL,8,Fyou became obsessed to the point of
OL,9,Fcriminality in stalking Stephanie
OL,10,FGlynn to provide evidence of her
OL,11,Faffair to weaponise that against her
OL,12,Ffor having that affair, and you also
OL,13,Fbecame determined to destroy the
OL,14,Fcareer of Andrew McLullich.
OL,16,F"In that obsession the feelings,
OL,17,Fembarrassment and pain felt by
OL,18,FStephanie Glynn were collateral
OL,19,Fdamage. You were more concerned about
OL,20,Fyour own feelings and a raging sense
OL,21,Fof injustice."
