OL,7,FHe said: "It was a further gross
OL,8,Fexample of stalking designed to
OL,9,Fmaximise their humiliation to your
OL,10,Fadvantage. Your conduct was intended
OL,11,Fto maximise fear or distress. You
OL,12,Fresorted to stalking out of a sense of
OL,13,Fvengeance for being the victim of an
OL,14,Faffair. I am sure the distress caused
OL,15,Fto your victim has been very serious."
OL,17,FBut he added that there was "another
OL,18,Fside" to the defendant who had no
OL,19,Fprevious convictions, and had suffered
OL,20,Fmental trauma himself.
