OL,7,FJudge Potter told the defendant: "The
OL,8,Fmost significant factor that means
OL,9,Fyour sentence will be suspended is the
OL,10,Feffect it would have on others, in
OL,11,Fparticular your son and your parents.
OL,12,FBut for those circumstances you would
OL,13,Fbe facing an immediate custodial
OL,14,Fsentence."
OL,16,FMs Glynn, now divorced, was said to be
OL,17,F"sickeningly anxious" as a result of
OL,18,FHarper's stalking and told the jury
OL,19,Fshe "constantly looked over her
OL,20,Fshoulder", had changed her routes to
OL,21,Fwork and had undergone counselling.
